		<category><![CDATA[Smart School]]></category>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">https://techcabal.com/?p=186095</guid>

					<description><![CDATA[Enugu is building 260 smart schools across the state, combining technology, funding, and curriculum reform to tackle deep-rooted learning gaps and modernise public education.]]></description>
										<content:encoded><![CDATA[
<p>On the outskirts of Enugu city in Southeastern Nigeria, the state government is developing new schools in communities where classrooms have long faced challenges such as inadequate infrastructure and outdated curricula. The buildings are clean-lined and modern, fitted with interactive boards, science labs, digital libraries, and innovation studios. </p>



<p>In some, children who once hawked goods in markets now sit behind desks, tapping through lessons on computer screens.</p>



<p>The state government says it wants to build 260 smart schools, one in each ward,&nbsp; one of the most ambitious public education reforms in Nigeria today, aimed at improving classrooms and restructuring key elements of the system. That intent is backed by money: 32.27% of the state’s 2026 budget has been earmarked for education, <a href="https://www.premiumtimesng.com/regional/ssouth-east/871882-enugu-abia-and-ebonyi-lead-south-east-education-spending-in-2026-budgets.html#:~:text=Despite%20the%20increased%20allocations%2C%20only,and%20Cultural%20Organisation%20(UNESCO)." target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener nofollow">the highest allocation by any Nigerian state</a>.</p>



<p></p>



